parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure - Alternator and Battery Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator and battery can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to potential accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure - Circuit Breaker and Fuse Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The overheating of the circuit breaker or fuse can cause electrical system malfunctions, potentially leading to fires or electrical shocks.
symptoms: Power seats and power doors are inoperative
burns or electrical shocks can occur when attempting to replace fuses.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ECM can cause the vehicle to not start, leading to potential accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
The stalling of the engine can cause potential accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the spark plugs can cause engine performance issues, potentially leading to stalling or difficulty starting the vehicle.
The failure of the seat belt latch can cause the seat belt to become unlatched during an accident, resulting in injury or ejection from the vehicle.
symptoms: The seat belt becomes unlatched during an accident
the seat belt does not lock
the seat belt buckle sticks and cannot be released
the seat belt buckle separates and will not latch properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Insufficient seat belt tension can lead to inadequate restraint during an accident, increasing the risk of injury or ejection from the vehicle.
symptoms: The seat belt has no tension
the seat belt does not provide adequate restraint during an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Design Flaw in Seat Belt Attachment
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A design flaw in the seat belt attachment can cause the occupant to be ejected from the vehicle if the door opens during an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt attachment to the door is defective
allowing the occupant to fall out of the vehicle if the door opens during an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Incorrect or incomplete recall information can lead to inadequate repair or replacement of defective seat belts, increasing the risk of injury or ejection from the vehicle.
symptoms: denied recall due to wrong information.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause sudden loss of power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: vehicle starts to smoke under the hood

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine mount failure can cause the engine to drop to the ground, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
Cooling system failure can cause engine overheating, leading to engine damage and potential failure.
Belt failure can cause engine damage and potential failure.
Exhaust system corrosion can cause exhaust system failure, leading to potential safety hazards.
The failure of the cradle bolts can cause the loss of steering control, leading to accidents and potential injuries.
symptoms: The front of the car lurches
and the frame is hanging down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The peeling of paint can lead to rust and corrosion, which can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle.
The failure of the door hinges can cause the door to fall off, leading to accidents and potential injuries.
symptoms: The door hinge breaks and falls off

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydraulic lift/shock can cause the vehicle to lose support, leading to accidents and potential injuries.
symptoms: sliding off and providing weak support.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver's side seat mounting can cause the seat to become unstable, rock back and forth, or even break away from the chassis, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The driver's side seat feels loose
the seat slides or rocks when applying brakes
the seat is reclined to the back position
the seat travels excessively on its rails
